FT  20 AUG 93 / Armenian forces capture Cebrayil
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRYSTIA FREELAND and Agencies
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Azerbaijan yesterday announced that Armenian forces captured the strategic
southern city of Cebrayil and were within striking distance of the Iranian
border, writes Chrystia Freeland in Moscow and agencies.
If the Armenian forces - pushing down from the disputed enclave of
Nagorno-Karabakh - reach the border they will cut off a huge swathe of
southern Azerbaijan. According to a statement released by the Azeris,
