FT  20 AUG 93 / Italian funding repayment offer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Former Italian health minister Francesco De Lorenzo, one of the most reviled
figures in the country's huge corruption scandal, was quoted yesterday as
offering to repay L4bn (Pounds 1.67m) in illegal funding he received, Reuter
reports from Rome. 'The illegal contributions amount to some L4bn. I will
give them back, selling what I can,' he told the Corriere della Sera
newspaper in an interview.
