<HEADLINE>
FT  20 AUG 93 / World News in Brief: Data 'held illegally'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Up to 100,000 UK organisations are illegally holding personal details on
computer, according to a National Audit Office report on data protection
controls. As many as 250,000 bodies are estimated to hold personal
information, yet only 150,000 have registered under the 1984 Data Protection
Act.
