<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 93 / Sudan on 'terrorist' list
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US yesterday formally added Sudan to a list of nations it accuses of
sponsoring terrorism, Reuter reports from Washington. The list already
includes Iran, Iraq, Syria, Libya, Cuba and North Korea. It makes Khartoum
ineligible for non-humanitarian US aid or for the commerical sales of US
arms or technology that could equip terrorists, and it requires Washington
to veto World Bank loans to Sudan.
