<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 93 / International Company News: Write-offs hit net at Leighton
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BIG write-offs on properties and a withdrawal from the US market hit the
results of Leighton Holdings, the Australian construction group, in the year
ended to June.
The company yesterday announced a 33 per cent fall in net earnings, to
ADollars 15.1m on a marginal decrease in revenue. The dividend is being held
at 8 cents a share.
The result followed abnormal losses of ADollars 64.4m, reflecting provisions
against properties and write-downs of US operations.
The abnormals are not expected to be repeated in the current year, Leighton
said. It expects increased net earnings for 1993-94.
