<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Ovoca Resources
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ovoca Resources, the Dublin-based exploration group, incurred losses of
IPounds 7,823 (Pounds 7,281) before and after tax over the 12 months to
December 31.
The outcome compared with a deficit of IPounds 519,479, of which IPounds
500,000 represented exploration expenditure written off.
The group, shares of which are traded on Dublin's Exploration Securities
Market and under Stock Exchange Rule 535 (2), is principally involved in
processing for gold but also seeks base metals and minerals in Ireland,
Brazil and Ghana.
Losses per share worked through at 0.06p (4p).
