<HEADLINE>
FT  19 AUG 93 / UN plans Somalia build-up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE United Nations peacekeeping force in Somalia needs to be boosted by
another brigade of about 3,000 men, secretary-general Boutros Boutros Ghali
said yesterday, agencies report from New York.
In a report to the Security Council asking for more men, he said Somali
factions and warlords must be disarmed and 'criminal elements' brought to
justice. He said fugitive warlord Mohammed Farah Aideed must bear the blame
for much recent strife.
The UN force is already set to rise next month to 28,000 soldiers from 27
countries. UN troops took over in May from a US-led force that numbered
37,000 at its peak.
