<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 93 / International Company News: Dell Computer posts first loss
after charges
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DELL Computer, the personal computer manufacturer, reported its first
quarterly losses after charges of Dollars 71m to cover restructuring,
inventory write-offs and other adjustments for delayed and cancelled
products.
Losses for the quarter were Dollars 75.7m, or Dollars 2.03 a share, compared
with net income of Dollars 21.9m, or 57 cents, in the same period last year.
Revenues rose to Dollars 701m from Dollars 458m.
Dell, until now one of the fastest-growing companies in the computer
industry, had previously acknowledged problems with the development of
notebook computer products and announced plans for restructuring charges.
Other factors contributing to the second-quarter loss included a
'significant sell-off of excess inventory at substandard (profit) margins,'
the company said.
