<HEADLINE>
FT  18 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Two banks to advise on Brent Walker
disposal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRENT WALKER, the property and leisure group, yesterday announced the
appointment of two merchant banks to advise it on the possible flotation of
William Hill, which might value the betting shop chain at over Pounds 500m.
The banks are Hill Samuel, which is Brent Walker's existing adviser, and NM
Rothschild.
William Hill has to repay a Pounds 350m loan by March 1 1994, and a
flotation is one way of raising the money. Brent Walker has received a cash
bid of Pounds 360m for William Hill from a consortium of investors, led by
SG Warburg.
However, Brent Walker is keen to retain a stake in William Hill and had
talked of maintaining a 40 per cent shareholding. Bankers believe it would
not be possible for Brent Walker to keep more than a small interest or 'the
sums don't work out,' one said. Potential investors are likely to want to
see William Hill managed independently from Brent Walker and financially
viable on a stand-alone basis.
Brent Walker bought William Hill for Pounds 685m in 1989 from Grand
Metropolitan but is trying to reclaim Pounds 200m of the purchase price.
</TEXT>
